---
title: Vessels & Vehicles
description: Learn about the Land Shark Tours fleet — Hydra Terra amphibious vehicles that are U.S. Coast Guard certified, virtually unsinkable, and unlike any other tour vehicle in the world.
keywords: Land Shark Tours vessel, Hydra Terra amphibious vehicle, Santa Barbara amphibious tour vehicle, Coast Guard certified tour boat, Land Shark amphibian
---

{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}

{% block content %}

  {% include "components/page-hero.njk" %}

  <section class="py-12 lg:py-16 bg-teal-50 -mt-2">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-4 lg:px-6">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 items-start">

        <!-- Left sidebar: specs card -->
        <div class="hidden lg:block w-80 shrink-0 fade-up">
          <div class="bg-navy-900 text-white rounded-2xl p-6">
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-5">Vessel Specs</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/10 pb-4">
                <span class="text-navy-200">Length</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-teal-300">39'</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/10 pb-4">
                <span class="text-navy-200">Width</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-teal-300">8.5'</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/10 pb-4">
                <span class="text-navy-200">Passengers</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-teal-300">45</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/10 pb-4">
                <span class="text-navy-200">Speed at Sea</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-teal-300">9 kts</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/10 pb-4">
                <span class="text-navy-200">Speed on Land</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-teal-300">70 mph</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/10 pb-4">
                <span class="text-navy-200">Engine</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-teal-300">300hp CAT</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-navy-200">Certified</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-teal-300">USCG &amp; DMV</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: main content -->
        <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">

          <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-navy mb-6 fade-up">The Hydra-Terra</h2>

          <div class="space-y-5 text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed stagger-children">
            <p>The Land Sharks are Hydra Terras — purpose-built amphibious vehicles manufactured in New York State. These aren't old military DUCKs from World War II. They're modern 2003 &amp; 2015 vessels designed specifically for the tourist industry, and are both DMV and U.S. Coast Guard certified, inspected, and approved.</p>
            <p>One of only about 80 worldwide, the Hydra-Terra is the only amphibious vessel with positive buoyancy foam-filled compartments — meaning it stays afloat even with drain plugs removed and full engine room flooding. The U.S. Coast Guard has verified it to be more stable in the water than any other amphibious vehicle in the world.</p>

            <div class="pt-2">
              <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">On Land</h3>
              <p>Powered by 300hp Caterpillar ultra-low emissions diesel engines with Allison transmissions, Anti-Lock disc brakes, and electronic steering. Capable of up to 70 mph on land. Operated by commercial drivers holding a Class B CDL with bus certification, as required by the California DMV.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-navy mb-2">On Water</h3>
              <p>Cruising at 9 knots, each vessel is operated by a U.S. Coast Guard Licensed Master Captain with a first mate and tour guide on board. All crew are trained in safety procedures, first aid, and CPR, and are DOT drug tested per U.S. Coast Guard requirements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Leaf CTA -->
          <div class="flex overflow-hidden w-full mt-10 fade-up" style="border-radius: 99px 5px 99px 5px; min-height: 200px;">
            <div class="w-1/2 shrink-0 relative">
              <img src="{{ "/assets/images/boat-1.jpg" | url }}" alt="" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="w-1/2 bg-blue-600 flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-white text-center px-8 gap-4">
              <p class="font-heading text-2xl lg:text-3xl leading-snug">Ready to ride a Land Shark?</p>
              <a href="https://book.{{ client.bookingDomain }}.com/{{ client.rgPath }}/reservations/calendar" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary">
                Book Now
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

{% endblock %}
